<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="205" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1794</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">French Ambassador</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1969</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-16">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 16, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge
                            the receipt of your note of August 4, 1917, relative to the proposals of
                            the Japanese Government concerning a consortium loan to China.</p>
                        <p>In reply to your request for an expression of opinion as to the views of
                            the Government of the United States on the subject discussed in your
                            note I have the honor to state that the matter is having at present the
                            careful consideration of this Government which cannot at this time
                            express an opinion relative thereto.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>